# WP Code Check - Public Repository .gitignore
# Protects user-generated content and proprietary information

# ============================================
# USER-GENERATED CONTENT (Never commit these)
# ============================================

# Log files from scans (may contain file paths and code snippets)
dist/logs/*.log
dist/logs/*.json
!dist/logs/.gitkeep

# HTML reports from scans (may contain proprietary code)
dist/reports/*.html
!dist/reports/.gitkeep

# User-created project templates (contain absolute paths)
dist/TEMPLATES/*.txt
!dist/TEMPLATES/_TEMPLATE.txt
!dist/TEMPLATES/_AI_INSTRUCTIONS.md
!dist/TEMPLATES/README.md
!dist/TEMPLATES/.gitkeep

# Baseline files (contain project-specific findings)
# Exception: Test fixture baseline is needed for CI tests
!dist/tests/fixtures/.hcc-baseline
.hcc-baseline
*.hcc-baseline
**/.hcc-baseline

# IRL (In Real Life) examples - user-generated real-world code samples
# Keep: folder structure and documentation
# Ignore: actual code files (may contain proprietary code)
dist/tests/irl/*
!dist/tests/irl/
!dist/tests/irl/README.md
!dist/tests/irl/_AI_AUDIT_INSTRUCTIONS.md
!dist/tests/irl/.gitkeep

# Auto-generated pattern library files (managed by pattern-library-manager.sh)
# The main JSON/Markdown artifacts are generated as needed; temp files are
# cleaned up automatically but we ignore any that leak through.
dist/PATTERN-LIBRARY.json
dist/PATTERN-LIBRARY.md
dist/PATTERN-LIBRARY.json.tmp.*
dist/PATTERN-LIBRARY.md.tmp.*

# Data analysis temporary files (from STANDARDIZED DATA ANALYSIS PATTERN)
# See AGENTS.md for usage guidelines
data-stream.json
data-stream-*.json
data-stream.txt
data-stream.csv

